  "text": "The ext_authz filter in Envoy implements comprehensive external authorization with bypass, passthrough, and caching controls across HTTP and network layers.\n\n## Key Bypass and Passthrough Controls:\n\n### Per-Route Bypass Configuration:\n- **FilterConfigPerRoute** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h): Implements per-route/per-virtualhost configuration with `disabled()` method that allows selectively skipping authorization checks for specific routes\n- **Filter::getPerRouteFlags()** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc:810-827): Retrieves per-route bypass flags from route metadata, supporting route-specific authorization bypass\n- **Filter::skip_check_** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h:367): Per-filter instance flag tracking whether authorization should be skipped\n\n### Global Bypass Control:\n- **FilterConfig::filterEnabled()** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h:101-106): Runtime-based and metadata-based global filter enable/disable mechanism\n- **FilterConfig::denyAtDisable()** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h:108-110): Feature flag to deny requests when filter is disabled\n- **Filter::decodeHeaders()** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc:226-277): Entry point implementing bypass logic - returns immediately if skip_check_ is set or filter is disabled\n\n### Authorization Decision Handling:\n- **Filter::onComplete()** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc:403-769): Central handler for authorization responses with three outcomes:\n  - CheckStatus::OK: Allows request with optional header mutations and route cache clearing\n  - CheckStatus::Denied: Sends local deny response with 403 status\n  - CheckStatus::Error: Implements failure-mode-allow passthrough if configured\n\n### Route Cache Management:\n- **FilterConfig::clearRouteCache()** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h:73): Configuration flag for clearing route cache when authorization modifies request headers\n- **onComplete() route cache clearing** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc:436-442): Clears route cache on OK responses with header modifications\n\n### Immediate Response Path:\n- **Filter::rejectResponse()** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc:771-784): Sends immediate 500 error response when authorization response is invalid\n- **sendLocalReply() calls** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc:717-735, 762-764, 781-783): Implements immediate local responses for Denied, Error, and Invalid cases\n\n### Passthrough and Request Continuation:\n- **Filter::continueDecoding()** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc:800-808): Resumes filter chain iteration after authorization completion\n- **failure_mode_allow** configuration (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h:178): Allows requests when authorization service is unavailable\n- **failure_mode_allow_header_add** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h:179): Adds special header on failure-mode-allow passthrough\n\n### Request Body Buffering and Timing:\n- **buffer_data_** and **max_request_bytes_** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h:362-366): Controls request body buffering for authorization service\n- **decodeData()** and **decodeTrailers()** (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc:279-311): Manage buffered data flow and authorization call initiation\n\n### Common Response Interface:\n- **Response struct** (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz.h:86-129): Unified authorization response with status, headers mutations, and query parameter modifications\n- **CheckStatus enum** (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz.h:69-76): Three-state decision (OK, Denied, Error)\n- **Client interface** (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz.h:146-168): Abstracts gRPC and HTTP authorization backends\n\n### Implementation Backends:\n- **GrpcClientImpl** (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz_grpc_impl.h): gRPC-based authorization service client\n- **RawHttpClientImpl** (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz_http_impl.h): HTTP-based authorization service client\n- **ClientConfig** (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz_http_impl.h): HTTP client configuration with header matchers\n\n### Network Layer Authorization:\n- **Network Filter** (source/extensions/filters/network/ext_authz/ext_authz.h): TCP/network-level authorization with similar bypass/passthrough/failure-mode logic\n- **Network Config Factory** (source/extensions/filters/network/ext_authz/config.cc): Creates network layer ext_authz filters\n\n### Request Validation:\n- **CheckRequestUtils** (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/check_request_utils.h): Builds authorization check requests from HTTP/TCP context\n- **Mutation Rules** (source/extensions/filters/common/mutation_rules/mutation_rules.h): Validates header mutations for security compliance\n\nThe implementation provides multiple layers of control: per-route bypass via route configuration, global bypass via metadata matching and runtime flags, immediate response generation for authorization decisions, request buffering for body inclusion, and failure-mode-allow passthrough for service unavailability scenarios."
